Steakhouse Steak
Cooking Light Jan/Feb 2006, p. 186

Rub:
1 tbsp  whole black peppercorns
1 tsp   kosher salt
1 tsp   dry mustard
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/4 tsp dried thyme

Meat:
1 lb    steak

Heat a small skillet over medium heat.  Add peppercorns; cook 1 minute or
until fragrant.  Grind peppercorns until fine.  Combine ground pepper, salt,
mustard, garlic powder, and thyme in a small bowl.  Rub mixture evenly over
steak.  Let stand 10 minutes.

Heat a nonstick grill pan over medium-high heat.  Coat the flank steak with
cooking spray; grill 7 minutes on each side or until desired degree of
doneness.  Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
